<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Richard P. Miller was editor and publisher of the <title render="italic"> Daily Tribune</title>, a south Oakland County, Michigan, newspaper. He succeeded his father Philip F. Miller who died in 1970.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection consists mainly of clippings of his column "Personally Speaking" and the editorials that he wrote for the newspaper.  There is also a small folder of biographical material.</p>
</scopecontent>

